1. Requirements Analysis

A. Duty Shifts:

    Long Day (L): 7:00 AM – 7:00 PM (12 hrs)

    Night (N): 7:00 PM – 7:00 AM (12 hrs)

    24 Hours (24): 7:00 AM – 7:00 AM (24 hrs)

    Off / Leave: No duty assigned.

B. Manpower Requirements:

    Ratios (Day/Night): 3:3, 3:2, or 4:3 (depending on doctor availability and hospital load).

C. Working Hours Rules:

    Full Time: 240 hours/month.

    2 in 1 (Half Time): 120 hours/month.

    Part-time: Individualized hours.

D. Crucial Duty Pattern Rules (Logic Constraints):

    Post-24h Rule: After a 24-hour shift, must have 1 or 2 days OFF.

    Sequential Constraint: Cannot do a Long Day (L) immediately followed by a 24-hour shift.

    Night Shift Constraint: Cannot do a Night (N) immediately followed by a 24-hour shift.

    Fatigue Management: Maximum 3 consecutive Long Days (L) or 3 consecutive Night Shifts (N).

    Mandatory Rest: Minimum 4 days OFF per month.

2. App Flow & Architecture

A. User Roles:

    Admin: Configures doctor profiles, setting monthly hour targets, and generating/editing the schedule.

    Doctor: Views their own personal schedule, requests leave, and marks availability.

B. App Flow:

    Dashboard: Monthly overview of shift coverage.

    Doctor Management: Profile creation (Full-time vs Part-time status).

    Scheduling Engine:

        Manual Mode: Admin assigns shifts via a grid.

        Auto-Generate (Advanced): Algorithm suggests assignments based on the patterns above.

    Conflict Checker: Real-time validation. If an admin assigns an 'N' followed by a '24', the app shows a "Fatigue Warning."
